Cell.Text: I've spent most of my life as a trader. I've got a stake in several shipping ventures across Tamriel, mostly imports and exports. | I made a lot of friends in a lot of ports, and the Thalmor approached me with a generous offer. | I give them access to my business associates, and they keep my coffers full.

Node.Caption: MQ201PartyRazelanFortuneTopic: How did you make your fortune?

Cell.Text: I trust them completely, because I understand them. | When the Thalmor want something, they tell you straight. In my experience, they have no interest in subtleties and innuendo. | So if one of them says they're going to do something, I believe them. When you can just take what you want, there's no need to lie.
Ah, pardon me, friend. I didn't see you standing there. | Allow me to introduce myself: Razelan. Imports and exports, by trade. Observer of human nature, by avocation.
G|Your wish is my command! As long as it doesn't involve much physical activity. I seem to be having trouble staying on my feet at the moment.

Node.Caption: MQ201PartyDrunkThanks: Thanks. I'll let you know if I need anything.

Cell.Text: Wonderful! I can begin to repay your generosity immediately. Say on, friend.

Node.Caption: MQ201PartyDrunkNeedHelp: Actually, there is something you could do for me.

Cell.Text: [S] G|Is that all? My friend, you've come to the right person. You could say that causing a scene is somewhat of a specialty of mine. | Stand back and behold my handiwork.

Node.Caption: MQ201PartyDrunkHowToHelp: I need you to cause a scene. Get everyone's attention for a few minutes.

Cell.Text: There's something you could do for me.
Of course! I would do anything for you, my one and truest friend! What do you need from me?
Here, I brought you a drink.
[S] Ah, the one generous soul amongst a gathering of pinch-pennies and lick-spittles! | If there's anything I can ever do for you, do not hesitate to call upon me!
Here, I brought you a drink.
[S] Ah, the nectar of the gods! If there's ever anything I can do for you, just name it!

My friend, you are very perceptive! I have a powerful thirst that cannot be slaked! | And none of the waiters will bring me a drink. Elenwen must have told them to cut me off, the frigid bitch. | Afraid I'll cause another scene, I suppose...
Indeed. Being a drunken boor is thirsty work. And I can't seem to find my way back to the bar...

You must be new around here. Bad manners to ask such a direct question, at one of Elenwen's little soirees. | But I have nothing to hide. I'm in from the south, on business. | And if you want to do business in Tamriel these days, well, you'd better get used to cozying up to the Thalmor. Like it or not.

Node.Caption: MQ201RazelanWhoAreYouTopic: What brings you to this party?

Cell.Text: G|Please. You first. I insist.
G|I just need to rest a moment, right here on this lovely rock.
G|Inside, my friend, inside! Where only the women and drinks are cold.
G|Stand back and watch a true professional wreck a party.

My friend! A toast to a beautiful friendship!
